The paper deals with algorithms for computing the partition function of a polynomial on the Boolean cube, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves techniques from discrete mathematics and information theory, which suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses Lipschitz constants and approximation algorithms, which are topics in machine learning and optimization, respectively, indicating cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories.
